- Hello, Terry.

936
01:19:43,734 --> 01:19:47,090
I told her I didn't know whether
or not she'd be with us today.

937
01:19:47,174 --> 01:19:49,165
Fooled you, Father.

938
01:19:51,054 --> 01:19:53,284
Ken, I told Father McGrath about us.

939
01:19:56,694 --> 01:19:59,845
He's going to find me ajob.
Aren't you, Father?

940
01:19:59,934 --> 01:20:05,611
- You'd better get well first, Terry.
- He's right. Then I'll try and find something.

941
01:20:06,174 --> 01:20:08,165
Take it easy.

942
01:24:11,374 --> 01:24:13,046
- Miss McKay.
- Yes?

943
01:24:13,134 --> 01:24:16,410
I wanna thank you for what
you're doin' for my son, Tyrone.

944
01:24:16,494 --> 01:24:18,883
Now he won't grow up to be a mug like me.

945
01:24:18,974 --> 01:24:21,124
You're too modest, Mr Bugsy.

946
01:24:21,214 --> 01:24:25,366
No, I ain't. I'm so stupid, I ain't even ignorant.

947
01:24:26,374 --> 01:24:30,845
- Thanks again.
- Thank Father McGrath. He got me the job.

948
01:24:30,934 --> 01:24:32,925
Thanks, Father.

949
01:24:37,054 --> 01:24:42,287
All eyes on me, please. As you know, poor
Molly has the measles, so I'll sing her part.

950
01:24:42,374 --> 01:24:44,524
Now, are we ready?

951
01:24:49,214 --> 01:24:51,205
Well, <i>now</i> we're ready.

952
01:24:51,974 --> 01:24:54,329
Watch me closely. We mustn't goof today.

953
01:28:22,174 --> 01:28:23,687
Well!

954
01:28:24,374 --> 01:28:26,365
Come in.

955
01:28:27,614 --> 01:28:31,402
Nickie! I'm so happy to see you. Come in.

956
01:28:31,894 --> 01:28:34,727
- How's my severest critic?
- Oh, well, we'll see.

957
01:28:34,814 --> 01:28:38,329
I see you've got them all arranged.
Let me hear the worst.

958
01:28:38,574 --> 01:28:41,884
Six months' work.
You haven't wasted your time, Nickie.

959
01:28:41,974 --> 01:28:45,284
Thank you. You should have seen
the 50 I dropped over the cliff.

960
01:28:45,374 --> 01:28:49,208
- Maybe you should have dropped this one.
- I'm inclined to agree with you.

961
01:28:49,294 --> 01:28:53,731
You know, I can read your state of mind
when you painted this.

962
01:28:53,814 --> 01:28:56,692
You were very sorry for yourself
when you painted this one.

963
01:28:56,774 --> 01:28:58,765
That one was painted in August.

964
01:29:00,414 --> 01:29:03,645
You were angry here.
You were getting over your broken heart.

965
01:29:03,734 --> 01:29:06,373
Broken heart? That stuff's not for me.

966
01:29:06,454 --> 01:29:08,968
- I'm glad to hear that.
- Let's get down this end.

967
01:29:09,054 --> 01:29:11,443
I'm coming to that. I'm coming to that.

968
01:29:14,574 --> 01:29:17,884
Here, Nickie, you became a painter.

969
01:29:18,574 --> 01:29:21,964
Thank you. I'm not exactly
ashamed of that one myself.

970
01:29:22,054 --> 01:29:25,046
I had a great deal to say -
and I painted it instead.

971
01:29:25,134 --> 01:29:29,730
Your being away, alone, for a long time
has given you that grasp of...

972
01:29:30,734 --> 01:29:33,806
I'll get it. Remember where you were.
I want to hear more.

973
01:29:33,894 --> 01:29:36,966
Hello. Courbet's Paint and Varnish Store.

974
01:29:37,814 --> 01:29:40,965
Nickie? I read you arrived today.

975
01:29:41,214 --> 01:29:44,570
Lois! How nice.
How did you know I was here?

976
01:29:44,974 --> 01:29:47,932
I called your hotel.
They said you were on this number.

977
01:29:48,014 --> 01:29:53,611
Nickie, I've been thinking about you morning,
noon and night, and in-between times too.

978
01:29:54,334 --> 01:29:56,643
I was wondering if maybe you could...

979
01:29:58,134 --> 01:29:59,647
Well...

980
01:29:59,774 --> 01:30:04,370
No, I like the idea all right - it's a nice offer.
But I can't make it this afternoon.

981
01:30:05,094 --> 01:30:08,564
Well, if you can't do that... I wish you would.

982
01:30:11,574 --> 01:30:15,044
Thanks anyway.
Nicest thing that's happened today.

983
01:30:16,094 --> 01:30:18,324
But you could make the show tonight.

984
01:30:18,974 --> 01:30:22,489
I'll leave a ticket at the box office anyway.
Do try to make it.

985
01:30:22,574 --> 01:30:24,485
And, Nickie...

986
01:30:24,574 --> 01:30:28,362
Whatever you do, don't plan
anything for <i>after</i> the show, huh?

987
01:30:56,294 --> 01:30:59,172
- I love our seats.
- What?

988
01:30:59,254 --> 01:31:01,245
I said "I love our seats."

989
01:31:26,494 --> 01:31:29,133
- We enjoyed it very much.
- Thank you for asking us.

990
01:31:29,214 --> 01:31:33,253
It was a pleasure. If you don't mind,
Mr Ferrante will see me home.

991
01:31:33,774 --> 01:31:35,765
Good night.

992
01:31:38,974 --> 01:31:43,286
- Where would you like to go?
- Suppose you decide. This is your evening.

993
01:31:43,374 --> 01:31:46,605
I've been away so long,
I have no idea where people go.

994
01:31:46,694 --> 01:31:48,685
My coat.

995
01:31:59,974 --> 01:32:01,566
Hello.

996
01:32:20,614 --> 01:32:22,969
Terry. Please let me tell him.

997
01:32:23,054 --> 01:32:25,045
No.

998
01:32:25,454 --> 01:32:28,366
- I'll go get him.
- No, no, please.

999
01:32:31,454 --> 01:32:33,684
It's pretty rough.

1000
01:32:33,774 --> 01:32:37,562
The first time you're able to get out,
you have to run into him.

1001
01:32:38,534 --> 01:32:41,731
And all I could say was..."Hello."

1002
01:32:46,334 --> 01:32:48,973
Well, the show's over.

1003
01:32:49,054 --> 01:32:51,045
The boy got the girl. Shall we go?

1004
01:32:55,894 --> 01:32:57,885
I'll only be a minute.

1005
01:33:19,574 --> 01:33:21,485
Good night, Lois, and thank you.

1006
01:33:21,574 --> 01:33:25,613
Taking you to a show tonight
wasn't a very good idea, was it?

1007
01:33:25,694 --> 01:33:29,403
- Merry Christmas, Lois.
- Merry Christmas, Nickie, and...

1008
01:33:30,094 --> 01:33:32,085
<i>auf Wiedersehen,</i>

1009
01:34:02,414 --> 01:34:07,488
I think it's terrible to have to take you home
just when everyone else is going out.

1010
01:34:10,174 --> 01:34:12,369
<i>C'est la vie,</i> Et cetera.

1011
01:34:14,214 --> 01:34:16,933
Terry, let me ask you again.

1012
01:34:17,014 --> 01:34:19,005
Why won't you let me help you?

1013
01:34:19,094 --> 01:34:22,245
All right, then, I will tell you again.

1014
01:34:22,334 --> 01:34:26,213
If you paid for my getting well,
he wouldn't like it, so I wouldn't like it.

1015
01:34:26,294 --> 01:34:29,730
Then if you did get me well
and I went to him, <i>you</i> wouldn't like it.

1016
01:34:29,814 --> 01:34:32,965
- But certainly he ought to know.
- No! If he found out,

1017
01:34:33,054 --> 01:34:36,888
he'd insist upon doing it himself -
if he had the money, which I doubt.

1018
01:34:36,974 --> 01:34:40,569
And then, if I didn't get well... that'd be awful.

1019
01:34:40,654 --> 01:34:46,126
No. Unless I can walk to him, and when I say
"walk" I mean "run", he'll never know.

1020
01:34:46,214 --> 01:34:49,809
Well, I'm fine. I've got my job
and I'm on a budget.

1021
01:34:49,894 --> 01:34:53,728
And if things come out right,
and then maybe if I'm a very good girl,

1022
01:34:53,814 --> 01:34:57,090
I'll get what I want <i>next</i> Christmas. Follow?

1023
01:35:20,534 --> 01:35:22,490
Merry Christmas.

1024
01:35:22,574 --> 01:35:24,565
How are you feeling, Miss McKay?

1025
01:35:25,694 --> 01:35:28,333
Children, I have bad news for you.

1026
01:35:29,174 --> 01:35:31,734
Doctor won't let me go with you.

1027
01:35:33,134 --> 01:35:35,807
Doctor, I could be back in a couple of hours.

1028
01:35:35,894 --> 01:35:38,124
This is the Christmas benefit.

1029
01:35:38,214 --> 01:35:41,286
This is their first public appearance.
This is my team.

1030
01:35:41,534 --> 01:35:44,844
- She's our coach, Doc.
- Norman! "Doctor."

1031
01:35:46,294 --> 01:35:48,285
She's our coach, Doctor.

1032
01:35:49,534 --> 01:35:52,287
If it wasn't good for her,
would you want her to go?

1033
01:35:52,374 --> 01:35:54,490
No.

1034
01:35:54,574 --> 01:35:57,964
Well, look. Why don't you
try it without me, hm?

1035
01:35:58,054 --> 01:36:01,364
Come on. The only thing
that would bother you would be the start.

1036
01:36:01,454 --> 01:36:03,729
- Miss McKay?
- Yes, Tyrone?

1037
01:36:04,494 --> 01:36:08,851
We'll be thinking about you while we sing,
hoping that you'll be around real soon.

1038
01:36:08,934 --> 01:36:10,925
Thank you, Tyrone.

1039
01:36:13,414 --> 01:36:16,884
Wait a minute. Where's Sally?
Isn't she with us today?

1040
01:36:16,974 --> 01:36:21,092
- We took her off. She sings too loud.
- She's a show-off.

1041
01:36:21,174 --> 01:36:25,929
Sally thought it was ajoke,
and she wanted so badly to go on the stage.

1042
01:36:27,534 --> 01:36:29,525
Come here, darling.

1043
01:36:29,694 --> 01:36:31,685
You go up on the stage with the others.

1044
01:36:31,774 --> 01:36:36,450
I'll put you back on the team, but you must
promise not to drown out the other children.

1045
01:36:36,534 --> 01:36:38,126
All right, Miss McKay.

1046
01:36:38,534 --> 01:36:40,331
- Are we ready?
- Yes.

1047
01:36:40,414 --> 01:36:42,405
All right.

1048
01:38:08,534 --> 01:38:13,369
- You're going to do all right without me.
- All right, children. We must go now.

1049
01:38:15,854 --> 01:38:18,243
- Merry Christmas.
- God bless you.

1050
01:38:18,334 --> 01:38:20,325
Be good, now.

1051
01:38:25,374 --> 01:38:29,367
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas, darling.

1052
01:38:33,214 --> 01:38:35,648
This isn't going to be
much of a Christmas for you.

1053
01:38:35,734 --> 01:38:38,612
- I'll be all right.
- There we are.

1054
01:38:38,694 --> 01:38:40,650
- Could just hand me my...
- Yes, surely.

1055
01:38:40,734 --> 01:38:42,725
Thank you so much.

1056
01:38:43,534 --> 01:38:47,288
You're welcome to have turkey
with my husband and me.

1057
01:38:47,374 --> 01:38:51,253
- You save a drumstick for me for later.
- All right, I will.

1058
01:38:51,334 --> 01:38:54,053
And if there's anything else
you want, just holler.

1059
01:38:54,134 --> 01:38:57,206
Thank you so much. I will.
It's very sweet of you.

1060
01:38:57,294 --> 01:39:00,570
- Merry Christmas.
- And a Merry Christmas to you too.

1061
01:39:01,774 --> 01:39:04,129
Does Miss McKay...

1062
01:39:14,694 --> 01:39:16,685
Hello, Terry.

1063
01:39:19,094 --> 01:39:21,562
It's... good to see you.

1064
01:39:22,454 --> 01:39:24,445
It's good to see you too.

1065
01:39:25,414 --> 01:39:29,885
- You feeling all right?
- Yes, yes. I'm fine. I'm just resting.

1066
01:39:29,974 --> 01:39:31,965
Good.

1067
01:39:32,734 --> 01:39:35,726
- It's been a long time.
- Yes, hasn't it?

1068
01:39:38,094 --> 01:39:40,449
Well, it is good to see you.

1069
01:39:40,534 --> 01:39:42,650
You said that.

1070
01:39:42,734 --> 01:39:45,123
- May I...
- Oh, yes. Please do sit down.

1071
01:39:48,214 --> 01:39:52,446
- I'll only be a minute. Sure you don't mind?
- No, of course not.

1072
01:39:54,454 --> 01:39:57,093
Oh, is this the breathtaking view?

1073
01:39:58,214 --> 01:40:00,853
Well, the altitude bothered me.

1074
01:40:08,854 --> 01:40:11,652
Well, I'll bet you're wondering how I got here.

1075
01:40:12,414 --> 01:40:14,405
Well, yes. Yes, I am.

1076
01:40:16,254 --> 01:40:20,725
I was looking through a telephone book
for a man named McBride

1077
01:40:20,814 --> 01:40:23,886
and I came across the name "T McKay".

1078
01:40:23,974 --> 01:40:28,604
I said to myself "Could that
possibly be Terry McKay, my old friend?"

1079
01:40:29,814 --> 01:40:32,453
- And it was.
- Yes.

1080
01:40:33,374 --> 01:40:38,402
And then I said to myself "Well, now,
I haven't been very nice to Miss McKay."

1081
01:40:38,494 --> 01:40:44,126
"After all, I had an appointment
with her one day, and I didn't keep it."

1082
01:40:46,094 --> 01:40:48,050
You didn't keep...

1083
01:40:48,134 --> 01:40:50,250
No.

1084
01:40:52,654 --> 01:40:57,011
So I said to myself -
I talk to myself quite a lot these days -

1085
01:40:57,094 --> 01:41:00,928
I said "That's not a very nice way
to treat an old friend like Miss McKay."

1086
01:41:01,014 --> 01:41:03,209
"I must apologise to Miss McKay."

1087
01:41:03,294 --> 01:41:07,924
Don't you agree, when someone doesn't
keep an appointment, they should apologise?

1088
01:41:08,014 --> 01:41:11,006
Yes. I think you're absolutely right.

1089
01:41:12,494 --> 01:41:18,524
I think the least people could do
is to say they're sorry, or... something.

1090
01:41:20,134 --> 01:41:22,125
So here I am.

1091
01:41:23,134 --> 01:41:26,285
- That's very sweet.
- I thought so.

1092
01:41:28,734 --> 01:41:32,773
I've often wondered about you.
And how you were.

1093
01:41:32,854 --> 01:41:34,845
Did you really?

1094
01:41:35,534 --> 01:41:38,048
Yes, really.

1095
01:41:38,654 --> 01:41:41,168
Well, I've often thought about you too.

1096
01:41:42,134 --> 01:41:45,285
Then you weren't angry
because I wasn't there?

1097
01:41:45,374 --> 01:41:47,524
I mean, you must have been at first.

1098
01:41:48,694 --> 01:41:50,685
Well...

1099
01:41:50,814 --> 01:41:52,805
Yes, I was.

1100
01:41:53,534 --> 01:41:56,094
At first I was furious.

1101
01:41:56,174 --> 01:41:59,291
I said "He can't do this to me.
Who does he think he is?"

1102
01:42:00,374 --> 01:42:03,286
How long did you wait?
I mean, did you wait long?

1103
01:42:05,014 --> 01:42:07,209
Well, let's... well, yes.

1104
01:42:07,294 --> 01:42:09,683
Yes, I waited until about...

1105
01:42:09,774 --> 01:42:11,844
Midnight.

1106
01:42:14,414 --> 01:42:16,882
And then what did you do?

1107
01:42:16,974 --> 01:42:19,534
Well, then I got really mad.

1108
01:42:20,414 --> 01:42:24,805
- You can imagine, standing up there on the...
- Yes, in a thunderstorm.

1109
01:42:26,534 --> 01:42:28,570
In a thunderstorm?

1110
01:42:30,574 --> 01:42:33,452
Then what did you say to yourself?

1111
01:42:33,534 --> 01:42:36,810
Then I said "I'll go on home and get tight."

1112
01:42:36,894 --> 01:42:39,203
- But you didn't do that.
- Didn't I?

1113
01:42:39,294 --> 01:42:44,448
No. Well, maybe just a little one,

1114
01:42:44,534 --> 01:42:46,525
every hour, for about a month.

1115
01:42:47,374 --> 01:42:50,207
- Can you blame me?
- I should say not.

1116
01:42:50,774 --> 01:42:53,925
The least I could have done
was to have sent you a note.

1117
01:42:54,014 --> 01:42:58,087
Perhaps, by the time you thought of it,
you didn't know where to reach me?

1118
01:42:58,174 --> 01:43:01,769
But you swore that if you ever
saw me again, you'd ask.

1119
01:43:01,854 --> 01:43:04,049
No.

1120
01:43:04,134 --> 01:43:07,843
I remember we said that if
we could make it, we'd be there.

1121
01:43:08,814 --> 01:43:13,683
And if one of us didn't show up,
it would be for a darn good reason.

1122
01:43:14,614 --> 01:43:18,163
- Did we say that?
- Yes, that is exactly what we said.

1123
01:43:18,254 --> 01:43:22,850
- Well, like what, for instance?
- So, there will be no more questions asked,

1124
01:43:22,934 --> 01:43:24,925
I hope?

1125
01:43:27,934 --> 01:43:30,050
Would you like a cigarette?

1126
01:43:30,134 --> 01:43:32,125
Thank you.

1127
01:43:32,214 --> 01:43:34,205
Thank <i>you,</i> Nickie.

1128
01:43:37,854 --> 01:43:41,642
Isn't that wonderful?
I walked all the way here just to...

1129
01:43:43,094 --> 01:43:47,053
And now I'm not even supposed
to ask you why you weren't there.

1130
01:43:48,774 --> 01:43:50,924
Isn't it strange?

1131
01:43:51,014 --> 01:43:53,926
We used to read each other's thoughts.

1132
01:43:54,014 --> 01:43:56,005
It's not the same, is it?

1133
01:43:56,614 --> 01:43:58,605
Not quite.

1134
01:43:59,414 --> 01:44:03,646
- It doesn't seem...
- I know.

1135
01:44:03,734 --> 01:44:06,487
I don't know what happens
to me whenever I...

1136
01:44:08,494 --> 01:44:10,485
No wedding ring, I see.

1137
01:44:11,734 --> 01:44:13,531
No.

1138
01:44:13,614 --> 01:44:16,447
- I thought at the...
- Last night, the show?

1139
01:44:17,054 --> 01:44:19,773
No, no. He was just...

1140
01:44:20,854 --> 01:44:22,845
No.

1141
01:44:24,214 --> 01:44:27,365
I didn't mean to offend you.

1142
01:44:27,454 --> 01:44:30,252
How's everything with you, Nickie?

1143
01:44:30,334 --> 01:44:33,132
Oh, you can ask questions!

1144
01:44:35,294 --> 01:44:38,843
I thought everything was fine
until I saw you last night.

1145
01:44:38,934 --> 01:44:43,883
Then I knew there must be <i>something</i>
between us, even if it's only an ocean.

1146
01:44:43,974 --> 01:44:45,965
So I bought myself a ticket.

1147
01:44:47,574 --> 01:44:50,088
Oh, you're sailing?

1148
01:44:50,894 --> 01:44:53,203
Tonight.

1149
01:44:54,734 --> 01:44:57,726
- And you're happy, aren't you?
- Yes.

1150
01:44:58,734 --> 01:45:00,804
- And you?
- I don't know.

1151
01:45:00,934 --> 01:45:03,767
I'm worried about the future,
and what people will think.

1152
01:45:03,854 --> 01:45:09,212
They'll say "There's the mad painter. What's
the matter with him? He doesn't like women."

1153
01:45:09,294 --> 01:45:12,809
- Why would people say that?
- Because he sails the seven seas,

1154
01:45:12,894 --> 01:45:18,207
and to every woman he meets, he says
"Where will you be in six months?"

1155
01:45:18,294 --> 01:45:20,285
- And they're there?
- Everywhere.

1156
01:45:20,374 --> 01:45:25,368
Tops of pyramids, domes of cathedrals, the
Eiffel Tower. He tries to keep them up high.

1157
01:45:25,454 --> 01:45:28,366
He keeps them waiting.

1158
01:45:28,454 --> 01:45:30,445
And where is he all this time?

1159
01:45:33,294 --> 01:45:35,728
Waiting.

1160
01:45:35,814 --> 01:45:37,964
But you can't go on like that.

1161
01:45:38,734 --> 01:45:43,489
It isn't right for you.
I wish I could say you were wrong.

1162
01:45:43,574 --> 01:45:46,372
I was once.

1163
01:45:47,814 --> 01:45:51,363
- How would you like to change the subject?
- Yes, I'd love to.

1164
01:45:51,454 --> 01:45:54,810
- Merry Christmas.
- Oh, I almost forgot.

1165
01:45:56,734 --> 01:46:01,649
Six months ago, who'd have thought
we'd be spending Christmas together?

1166
01:46:01,734 --> 01:46:03,725
I brought you a present.

1167
01:46:06,454 --> 01:46:10,413
Thank you. I'm sorry I don't have one for you.

1168
01:46:10,494 --> 01:46:13,566
I didn't think I'd be seeing you.

1169
01:46:13,654 --> 01:46:18,887
That's all right, I didn't expect one.
That isn't really a Christmas present.

1170
01:46:28,054 --> 01:46:30,284
Oh, that's why my letters came back.

1171
01:46:38,174 --> 01:46:42,486
I would have sent it to you,
but I didn't know your address until today.

1172
01:46:45,054 --> 01:46:47,693
She wanted you to have it, remember?

1173
01:46:49,974 --> 01:46:53,284
So... that's the reason I...

1174
01:47:04,854 --> 01:47:06,845
Goodbye, Terry.

1175
01:47:08,494 --> 01:47:10,485
Goodbye, Nickie.

1176
01:47:30,734 --> 01:47:33,373
You know, I painted you
like that, with the shawl.

1177
01:47:33,454 --> 01:47:37,333
I wish you could have seen it.
Courbet said it was one of my best.

1178
01:47:38,294 --> 01:47:44,210
I didn't think I could ever part with it, but
there was no reason to keep it any longer.

1179
01:47:44,294 --> 01:47:48,082
I couldn't take money for it
because, well, you know...

1180
01:47:48,174 --> 01:47:53,806
So Courbet told me a young woman
came into the gallery and... she liked it.

1181
01:47:54,054 --> 01:47:58,764
She saw in it what I'd hoped you'd see, so...
I told Courbet to give it to her.

1182
01:47:59,854 --> 01:48:04,405
Because he said she didn't have
any money, and not only that, she was...

1183
01:48:07,134 --> 01:48:09,125
She was...

1184
01:48:10,854 --> 01:48:13,493
Anyway, I told him to give it to her.

1185
01:48:13,574 --> 01:48:16,088
Courbet said she wanted it so badly and...

1186
01:48:16,174 --> 01:48:19,644
So I told him to give it to her.
It's the Christmas season and all that.

1187
01:48:19,734 --> 01:48:22,123
And you know me, holly in my heart.

1188
01:48:54,334 --> 01:48:56,484
Darling, don't look at me like that.

1189
01:49:00,854 --> 01:49:02,890
Why didn't you tell me?

1190
01:49:02,974 --> 01:49:06,933
If it had to happen to one of us,
why did it have to be you?

1191
01:49:11,614 --> 01:49:13,605
It was nobody's fault but my own.

1192
01:49:16,094 --> 01:49:18,085
I was looking up.

1193
01:49:19,054 --> 01:49:21,204
It was the nearest thing to heaven.

1194
01:49:23,134 --> 01:49:25,125
You were there.

1195
01:49:26,334 --> 01:49:28,325
Oh, darling.

1196
01:49:28,454 --> 01:49:31,014
Don't worry, darling.

1197
01:49:31,094 --> 01:49:33,972
If you can paint, I can walk.

1198
01:49:34,374 --> 01:49:37,286
Anything can happen, don't you think?

1199
01:49:37,374 --> 01:49:39,729
Yes, darling.

1200
01:49:46,934 --> 01:49:55,364
<i># A love affair to remember</i>

1201
